column3:
Oh, is that a Pokédex? You must be helping
{pageend:Professor Rowan.}
{pageend:What’s your name?}
...

OK—hello, {tag:0}. I’ll be sure to
{pageend:remember that name!}
{pageend:My name is Cynthia. I’m a Trainer just like you.}
I’ve been studying Pokémon mythology lately,
just out of curiosity.

Remember, you can use the hidden move Cut
{pageend:from your Pokétch in the field.}
It will let you go places that were previously
{pageend:inaccessible to you.}
That’s important for filling up your Pokédex,
right? Then luck be with you, young Trainer!

{pageend:Hey, you! Yeah, you, Trainer!}
{pageend:Errr... It’s OK. Never mind. You look tough.}
I won’t take— Um, I’ll just let you keep your
Pokémon. Carry on!

{pageend:Have you seen our building?}
Team Galactic is so stinking rich that we can
have one built instantly!

{pageend:Do you use bike stands?}
It looks so cool to hop off your bike and then
lean on it. It looks so smooth!

{pageend:They say this is an old city.}
It doesn’t look it, though. Not with all these
tall buildings.

Hey there! The Cycle Shop owner
{pageend:is looking for you.}
Why don’t you pay him a visit?

{pageend:Oh, don’t tell me you don’t have an Explorer Kit?}
You should have a word with the man next door
to the Pokémon Center.

{pageend:Oh wow! You got a bike!}
You can ride down Cycling Road and end up in
{pageend:Hearthome City.}
It’s a fast and fun ride. You should check it out!

{pageend:Oh wow! You got a bike!}
You can ride down Cycling Road and end up in
{pageend:Hearthome City.}
It’s a fast and fun ride. You should check it out!

{pageend:There is some writing on the Pokémon statue...}
Dia..., once created,
brought time into being.

...in laughter or in tears,
{pageend:the same time flows...}
Such is the blessing of Dia...

{pageend:There is some writing on the Pokémon statue...}
Pal..., once created, brought
forth the many dimensions.

All things—alive or not...—
{pageend:arri... at the same space.}
Such is the blessing of Pal...

Team Galactic took my Pokémon away.
{pageend:They took other people’s, too.}
Something should be done, but Team Galactic
{pageend:creeps everyone out...}
What are they doing to my Pokémon?

{pageend:I got my Pokémon back!}
I’m so happy, I feel like riding my bike down
Cycling Road together with it!

Hi, you cute little Trainer! What kinds of
{pageend:Pokémon are with you?}
Oh, your {tag:0}...

It’s the latest model, so I’ll read the operating
{pageend:manual to you.}
“Press the B Button to shift gears,” it says.

The manager’s gone off to the Team Galactic
{pageend:building and hasn’t returned.}
I wonder what’s holding him up.

{pageend:There is a manual on the latest model of bicycle.}
Third gear for steering.
{pageend:Fourth gear for all-out speed!}
Change gears with the B Button for
exhilarating cycling!

{pageend:There’s a catalog on bikes...}
The Mach Bike—a folding bike built solely for
blazing speed!

Welcome to Team Galactic. Are you here to
{pageend:donate your Pokémon?}
What? You’re not? Then kindly get off
{pageend:our property!}
Do we have to bring the pain like we did with
the Cycle Shop manager?

{pageend:Eh? Did you want something?}
How silly of me to even ask. You want to free the
Pokémon. Yeah, that’s gonna happen!

{pageend:Well, aren’t you tough...}
It’s OK, though. Our official Pokémon-statue
{pageend:investigation is finished.}
And Mars has collected energy from the
Valley Windworks.

I suggest you keep out of Team Galactic’s affairs
{pageend:from now on.}
This is your last warning!

{pageend:What is it with this Team Galactic?}
Why did they take our Pokémon? What are they
trying to accomplish?

{pageend:Anyway, they’re gone now. Thank you very much!}
I can’t thank you enough right now, but cruise by
my Cycle Shop, OK?

{pageend:Hello, hello! I am the official Name Rater!}
Want me to rate the nicknames of
your Pokémon?

{tag:0}, is it? That is a truly
{pageend:impeccable name!}
Take good care of {tag:1}!

Excuse me, but do you got that Pokémon
{pageend:named Snorunt?}
Wanna trade it for my Chatot?

Yes! So awesome! A Snorunt!
{pageend:I so promise I’ll be good to it!}
Oh yeah, Chatot can learn some human
{pageend:speech pretty quickly.}
Try out its move Chatter.
You’ll totally see what I mean.

Gardenia, our Gym Leader, goes out to Eterna
{pageend:Forest every so often.}
I always wonder what she does there.

Someone ought to invent herbal medicine that
{pageend:isn’t bitter.}
That would be a medical breakthrough!

Ah, it’s you! Good to see you! How is your
{pageend:Pokédex coming along?}
Catching every kind of Pokémon is no easy feat—
{pageend:I’ll grant you that.}
But I’m sure you can accomplish it!

{pageend:Ah, yes!}
An acquaintance from Kanto has sent me
{pageend:something quite interesting.}
I think you’d make better use of it than I
ever could.

{pageend:Have you seen the Pokémon statue?}
When I was a wee child, it used to be the
centerpiece of many festivals...

{pageend:Hey there!}
How’s it going,
{pageend:Champ-to-be?}
Actually, that’s what I said to some boy
who zipped in here earlier, too!

The Gym Leader, Gardenia,
{pageend:is a user of Grass-type Pokémon.}
Did you know that they can’t
{pageend:be affected by powder moves?}
{pageend:Oh, and be careful who you bring with you!}
I hear the Leader here has a trump card
that can mix you up with one right move.

Oh, wait a second,
{pageend:I should tell you about the Gym itself.}
You can’t challenge the Gym Leader
{pageend:until you beat all the Gym’s Trainers.}
It’s a bit challenging, but just think
of it as good training and go for it!

Eterna City Pokémon Gym
Gym Leader: Gardenia
Certified Trainers: {tag:0}

Eterna City Pokémon Gym
{pageend:Gym Leader: Gardenia}
Certified Trainers: {tag:0}
{tag:1}

{pageend:You kept me waiting!}
I’m Eterna’s Gym Leader, Gardenia, the Grass-
{pageend:type master!}
When I first saw you, I was convinced you’d find
your way to me.

My hunch was right on the money. You have a
{pageend:winning aura about you.}
So, anyway, this will be fun. Let’s have our battle!

{pageend:I might’ve said it before, but you’re really tough!}
Wasn’t it hard for you to raise your Pokémon to
be so good?

I guess that’s a measure of how much you love
{pageend:your Pokémon.}
In recognition of that, I proudly grant you this!

My Grass-type Pokémon can dole out
{pageend:some serious special attacks...}
I won’t let you win...easily!

Every time you beat a Trainer, the
{pageend:floral clock moves.}
{pageend:The fountain also stops if I lose.}
It’s so you can go to the Pokémon
Center during your challenge.

My gift to you, the Explorer Kit, will instantly
{pageend:take you to the Grand Underground!}
You need only to use it, and you will be down in
{pageend:the tunnels and caverns beneath our feet.}
Underground lies a different world where you can
do this, that, and the other thing, too!

How was it down in the Grand Underground?
{pageend:Big and empty, I would think.}
But that’s just because you’re a novice spelunker!

Try to get right atop the spot where a yellow
{pageend:light is shown on your radar, OK?}
Now, off you go on your treasure hunt!

Ah! I see you were able to use your radar
{pageend:effectively! Well done, indeed!}
Here’s your reward!

Dig in the walls of the Grand Underground to
{pageend:unearth hidden things.}
Treasure you find will go straight into your Bag!

Spheres are special gems that can be exchanged
{pageend:for goods down there.}
Now, what should I assign you next...?

{pageend:All you need is the Digger Drill I gave you earlier.}
Simply go to the Grand Underground and use
{pageend:the Digger Drill wherever you like.}
It will instantly create your very own Secret Base!

{pageend:Oh? You don’t know how to use the Digger Drill?}
OK, I’ll admit this test may have been a little
tricky for you.

Do that and you’ll have your Secret Base before
{pageend:you can say...}
<size=250%>Boo!</size>{pageend:}
No, but seriously, there are some walls you can’t
{pageend:dig through, like those at the corners of a tunnel.}
First, try to dig into different walls!

{pageend:Ah, you’ve made your Secret Base. Excellent!}
I thought I might have been asking too much of
{pageend:you, but you did it!}
Well done! Take these as your reward!

{pageend:By the by, a Digger Drill can only be used once.}
If you wish to move your Secret Base, you will
{pageend:need to obtain another Digger Drill.}
{pageend:You can trade spheres for one underground.}
Now, what should I have you do next...?

Aha! You managed to decorate your Secret Base.
{pageend:I knew I recognized a top-notch spelunker in you!}
Well done! This is your reward!

It seems you can find differently-colored lights
{pageend:when you communicate with other spelunkers.}
If you do find one, I’ll give you a rare pedestal.

{pageend:Oh, have you found a light of a different color?}
It seems you can find differently-colored lights
when you communicate with other spelunkers.

{pageend:There really is nothing else that I can teach you.}
Add more statues to your Secret Base, dig for
treasure, and become a master spelunker for me!

Oh! The look on your face tells me you found
{pageend:someone else’s Secret Base!}
Well done. Here’s your reward!

Statues set up in Secret Bases appear to impart
{pageend:mysterious effects.}
You can even get the power from someone else’s
{pageend:Secret Base!}
Don’t be shy! Make the power of statues yours!

{pageend:Let’s dig up some treasure!}
{pageend:I’m from Oreburgh. I work at the Mining Museum.}
I got advice from the Underground Man on
digging up Fossils and spheres.

{pageend:New and on sale: the underground radar!}
The radar indicates possible treasure locations.
Use this handy tool to track them down!

I’m Mira. I was catching Pokémon, and then I
{pageend:got lost. I’m so scared...}
Please! Please take me to the exit!

Oh! There’s the exit! I want to get tougher so I
{pageend:won’t be such a scaredy-cat.}
{tag:0}, bye-bye! Thank you!

I like helpful Pokémon moves, like Growl
{pageend:and Minimize.}
Those kinds of moves are my favorites.

{tag:0}, did you get to be so good
{pageend:because you’re always with your Pokémon?}
Yes! That has to be it! I’m gonna try—like you!

{tag:0}{pageend:, long time no see!}
Oh? You look puzzled. You’re wondering who
I am.

{tag:0}{pageend:, long time no see!}
Oh? You look puzzled. You’re wondering who
I am.

Oh, my! You’ve met {tag:0}{pageend: Pokémon!}
Wonderful! Yes, bravo! Professor Rowan should
{pageend:be delighted!}
Here is something for you!

You’ve met only {tag:0}{pageend: Pokémon?}
{pageend:Hmm... You’ve got to find at least 35.}
If you can’t, it will be tough to complete the
Sinnoh Pokédex.

But this isn’t about me! I’ve got something nice
{pageend:for you.}
{tag:0}, choose which hand you want.

{pageend:I see... You want the Vs. Seeker.}
I’m impressed, {tag:0}. You know
what’s important.

Oh, {tag:0}, do you also have
{pageend:a Pokétch?}
{pageend:Yup, you do. You can have this too, then.}
You deserve it for all your hard
work, {tag:1}.

{pageend:It will be especially useful inside dark caves.}
OK, let’s keep working on our Pokédexes.
Professor Rowan is counting on us!

Hey, {tag:0}! How’s your Pokédex
{pageend:coming along?}
Me? I’m doing great, as always... NOT!

{pageend:Oh yeah. You want the Vs. Seeker.}
Yup, {tag:0}, you know
what’s important.

{tag:0}, what about a Pokétch?
{pageend:Do you have one?}
{pageend:Yup, you do. You can have this too, then.}
You deserve it for all of your
effort, {tag:1}.

{pageend:Trainer Tips}
Pokémon may become immobilized if they are
asleep or paralyzed.

{pageend:But what became of that world?}
Because the human spirit is weak and
{pageend:incomplete, strife has spread...}
This world is being ruined by it...

{pageend:I’m hopelessly lost!}
Please don’t pay attention to a lowly grunt
without any Pokémon!

There’s no way of getting to the peak of
{pageend:Mount Coronet from this side!}
Uh-oh... Was I supposed to go up from the
{pageend:Hearthome City side?}
I can’t get up to the peak from the
Eterna City side?

{pageend:Well, that was just pathetic...}
We’re just gonna let you pass so you can get
pulverized by our bosses!

Everything is ready for the creation
{pageend:of a new world.}
Now, all will end.
{pageend:And everything will begin.}
With this, the Red Chain made from the
{pageend:crystals of the three lake Pokémon...}
And this, the Red Chain I replicated
{pageend:with technological means...}
With these Red Chains I will pry open
{pageend:the portal to another dimension.}
I command that you unleash your power
for me...

{pageend:I have captured both mythical deities.}
{pageend:Dialga and Palkia.}
{pageend:Now, all will end. And everything will begin.}
With this Red Chain, I will pry open the portal to
another dimension and summon...the true creator of Sinnoh!

{pageend:I command that you unleash your power for me—}
Giratina, the mythical Pokémon, and the master of
the universe!

I’ve waited so long for this
{pageend:moment, Dialga and Palkia.}
Shaping this world is a double spiral
{pageend:of time and space.}
Yes, the very things that you have the
{pageend:ability to control!}
You will do my bidding!
{pageend:I will have your abilities as mine!}
With the power I wield, I will create
an entirely new world!

The incomplete and ugly world we have
{pageend:now can disappear.}
I am resetting everything to zero.
{pageend:Nothing can remain.}
It is all for making the ultimate world.
{pageend:A world of complete perfection.}
Nothing so vague and incomplete as
spirit can remain.

This is the mythical Pokémon that
{pageend:created Sinnoh!}
Giratina, the ancient deity!

This world cannot be molded into the ultimate
{pageend:world I seek!}
It’s far easier to create an entirely new world
{pageend:than to change this one!}
A new world in which I am the ruler of all things!
I shall become a deity!

{pageend:And I’ll be next.}
You might be tough, but this time, the gloves are
coming off!

...I should have expected as
{pageend:much.}
{pageend:Uxie, “The Being of Knowledge.”}
{pageend:Azelf, “The Being of Willpower.”}
And Mesprit, “The Being of Emotion”...

The Pokémon have come to protect
{pageend:Sinnoh? Pathetic and worthless.}
It takes the three of them, the three
lake Pokémon that symbolize spirit,
to balance either the Pokémon of time
{pageend:or space.}
But they can’t maintain balance against
{pageend:the two.}
Not when both Dialga and Palkia are
{pageend:here.}
Their coming here is in vain.
So much meaningless drama.

Now, {tag:0}{pageend:.}
You’ve constantly interfered with my
{pageend:plans, but you will be forgiven.}
After all, there will remain no spirit
{pageend:for all time when I am done.}
All spirit will disappear.
{pageend:It will be ripped away...}
From you!
From your Pokémon!
{pageend:From those precious to you...!}
It is time!
My dream will be my reality!

{pageend:Telling you is meaningless. But I will not give up.}
I will become a deity one day, and I will make
the ultimate mine...

{pageend:Telling you is meaningless. But I will not give up.}
I will become a deity one day, and I will make
the ultimate mine...

{pageend:Giratina, the master of Reality...}
It’s impossible to tell if it is enraged
or saddened.

But to me, Giratina appears to be waiting for
you, {tag:0}{pageend:.}
It seems to be challenging you as a test...

Giratina is out of control after being dragged out
{pageend:by the Red Chain and forced to use its power.}
Giratina seems to be trusting you to stop it.

{pageend:Giratina, the master of Reality...}
It’s impossible to tell if it is enraged
or saddened.

But to me, Giratina appears to be waiting for
you, {tag:0}{pageend:.}
It seems to be challenging you as a test...

Giratina is out of control after being dragged out
{pageend:by the Red Chain and forced to use its power.}
Giratina seems to be trusting you to stop it.

{tag:0}... I ran into {tag:1}
{pageend:a little while ago.}
He said that he believed in you. He said that you
could get the job done.

Go to Route 209! Head to the Grand
{pageend:Underground! Listen to the stone pillar!}
Talk to spelunkers!

{pageend:Trainer Tips}
After a Berry is planted, watch the color of
{pageend:the soil.}
If the soil is dark, it means it has plenty of
moisture. If the soil is lighter in color, water it
with your Sprayduck.

{pageend:I’m Keira! I’m a Super Contest Show judge.}
Please drop by the Contest Hall so I can thank
you properly!

Oh, I’m so sorry! Please, excusez-moi.
{pageend:Are you entering a Super Contest Show?}
Ohoho... Enjoy yourself, please!

Hey, you’re a Trainer now. You’re expected to be
{pageend:ready for a battle. No whining! No waiting!}
Let’s get the show started!

It may also be of help to the completion of your
{pageend:Pokédex. I think you ought to go there.}
OK, bye-bye for now!

{pageend:You’re a Trainer, aren’t you?}
You’ve got two choices of challenges, either
the Gym or a Super Contest Show, right?

{pageend:I was given a TM for Strength at the Lost Tower.}
The Lost Tower is on Route 209 on the way to
Solaceon Town.

There are just so many Stickers to place on
{pageend:Ball Capsules.}
I can’t decide what I should use.

I went for a stroll in Amity Square with my
{pageend:Pachirisu today.}
{pageend:We came across a cute Sticker while we walked.}
Do you think placing this on my Pachirisu’s Ball
Capsule will make my Pachirisu look even cuter?

{pageend:Hi, hi. Do you want a Pokémon Egg?}
They found this at the Pokémon Nursery in
{pageend:Solaceon Town...}
Want to take it?

{pageend:This is what I heard about Eggs...}
If you take that Egg and travel with energetic
{pageend:Pokémon, it’ll hatch.}
I remember someone announced that...
Professor Elm of Johto maybe?

{pageend:I’ve heard there are lots of Stickers to be found.}
Someone told me that you can find some in
Amity Square.

{pageend:Hey there! How’s it going, Trainer?}
You being here tells me you’re going to
challenge the Gym Leader.

{pageend:So, where’s the Gym Leader, you ask?}
I can’t precisely say, but I have a hunch that she’ll
{pageend:return one day...}
{pageend:But only after you visit other places, I think.}
Hey, I’m sorry I’m not more useful. My advice-
giving needs work...

Hey there!
{pageend:How’s it going, Champ-to-be?}
The Gym Leader here is a user
{pageend:of Ghost-type Pokémon.}
Thanks to all her Super Contest Show training,
when her Pokémon get scared,
{pageend:they pick up the pace!}
Even the ones that aren’t fully-raised
{pageend:are a lot tougher than they look.}
Some might even endure what should be a decisive KO!

Oh! {tag:0}!
{pageend:You’ve beaten the Gym Leader!}
There seems to be no end to how tough you
{pageend:are getting! At least that’s how I see it!}
{pageend:...}
You do realize I say that to everyone, right?

Hearthome City Pokémon Gym
Gym Leader: Fantina
Certified Trainers: {tag:0}

Hearthome City Pokémon Gym
{pageend:Gym Leader: Fantina}
Certified Trainers: {tag:0}
{tag:1}

They hold contest shows in this city?
{pageend:I say to myself, enfin, I will excel.}
That is why I dress this way.
{pageend:C’est une performance!}
Also, I study Pokémon very much. I have come to
be Gym Leader.

{pageend:And, uh, so it shall be that you challenge me.}
But I shall win. That is what a Gym Leader
does, non?

{pageend:I am dumbfounded!}
So very, very strong! You, your Pokémon,
{pageend:so strong!}
Your power is admirable! I shall honor it with this
Gym Badge!

{pageend:Three Gym Badges...}
But you must not forget this: there are many
{pageend:other Trainers.}
Strong Trainers, too. There are many more
{pageend:in Sinnoh.}
Have patience! You must become stronger,
one at a time.

{pageend:Hello, do you have a Poffin Case?}
If you haven’t got one, you really must visit the
Pokémon Fan Club.

The Pokémon that’s holding the {tag:0}
{pageend:will regain HP a little by inflicting damage.}
It was given to me when I was on vacation, but I
already had one.

{pageend:Hello, hello! How, I say, do you do?}
I am the Pokémon Fan Club Chairman! Indeed,
yes I am!

{pageend:And why, I say, would I do that?}
Because the giving of Poffins is a way of
expressing your love!

In such ways I say that Poffins have nothing but
{pageend:goodness for Pokémon!}
{pageend:Therefore!}
I declare this Poffin Case to be a gift from me,
to you!

And why are we number one? Because I brag
{pageend:more than anyone!}
{pageend:But now I can’t brag as much...}
People started complaining, so I’ve had to curtail
my bragging...

{pageend:Hearthome City is a great place.}
Every year, it gets voted the most desirable place
to live in Sinnoh.

If you say Hearthome City, I only say this:
{pageend:Super Contest Shows!}
I’m going to enter my darling Pokémon in them!

{pageend:I’ve given my Pokémon lots of Poffins.}
I’m confident that we’ll win our share of Super
Contest Shows.

{pageend:Oh, wow, you’re a Pokémon Trainer.}
Having lots of Pokémon around is a lot
{pageend:of responsibility.}
But that also comes with a lot of fun!

A world in which people are compassionate
{pageend:to others...}
That’s all that matters to me.

{pageend:Hiya!}
Oh, I’ve seen you somewhere before! Where was
{pageend:it again? Hold on, it’ll come to me...}
Oh yeah! You’re the one who was battling those
{pageend:scary looking guys in Jubilife City!}
I was really curious about you after that, so I
went ahead and did a little research.

{pageend:Here you go!}
Wait, I can’t do that! You’ve completely filled up
{pageend:those Pokémon Boxes I made!}
I know it’s sad, but you need to go let one of
your Pokémon go and then come back!

{pageend:Hi! Let’s get cooking!}
Here’s my advice on cooking tasty Poffins for
{pageend:your Pokémon crew!}
In the beginning, while it’s still a batter, swirl it
gently and avoid spillage.

{pageend:Have you got some Berries?}
To make delicious Poffins, the key ingredient is a
{pageend:rare Berry.}
Also, Poffins will come out yummy if you cook
Berries as quickly as possible, but still slowly
enough that you don’t spill the batter.

Eating good food makes people and Pokémon
{pageend:more energetic and happy.}
In that sense, we’re exactly alike.

{pageend:Oh, I don’t know about that.}
I’ve never spoken to {tag:0} about
{pageend:Super Contest Shows.}
I’m surprised you two know each other, though.

Were you surprised to see me,
{tag:0}{pageend:?}
I got bored, so I came out to Hearthome for a
{pageend:little vacation.}
I’m just as surprised to see you here, my dear!

But are you serious about entering
{pageend:Super Contest Shows? Not dressed that way!}
It’s your Pokémon’s time to shine, so you
{pageend:shouldn’t just be dressed your usual way.}
Put this on for a little glamour.

I’m sure it will look good on you. After all, I
{pageend:chose it.}
{pageend:Go enjoy the Super Contest Shows, honey!}
Shows will give you a different look at the many
{pageend:charms of Pokémon.}
It should be an eye-opening experience for you.
Bye now!

Oh, and a word of advice. Go take a run at the
{pageend:contest shows!}
However, the best way to get ready is to get
{pageend:some practice first.}
You can take practice sessions at the counter
on the right.

Oh, and a word of advice for you. Go take a run
{pageend:at the contest shows!}
However, the best way to get ready is to get
{pageend:some practice first.}
You can take practice sessions at the counter
on the right.

Oh, and a word of advice. Go take a run at the
{pageend:contest shows!}
However, the best way to get ready is to get
{pageend:some practice first.}
You can take practice sessions at the counter
on the right.

{pageend:Hello! I’m with Jubilife TV!}
Was this your first Super Contest Show?
Did you have fun?

I may ask you to let us closely cover your story
{pageend:in the future.}
Oh, please take this!

{pageend:Things that people think are fun spread quickly.}
Good luck and take care!
Let me interview you again sometime!

{pageend:The art of crafting things fatigues one’s spirit.}
When the spirit is healed, the desire to make
{pageend:something returns.}
It is such a wondrous cycle.

Pokémon... People... It’s only natural that we are
{pageend:all so very different.}
Make sure that you never judge a Pokémon
{pageend:based on whether it’s weak or strong.}
You must always look for the good inside of
them. That’s what counts!

{pageend:Are you enjoying your stroll?}
You should try talking to your Pokémon.
It will be happy you did.

There is a broken, crumbling tower made
{pageend:of stone...}
There seems to be a spot that would be a
{pageend:perfect fit for the Odd Keystone.}
Would you like to use the Odd Keystone?

{pageend:Try fishing wherever there is a body of water.}
Oh, incidentally, do you need me to explain how
to use that fishing rod?

When I was jogging the other day, a wild
